&lt;figure>&lt;img src="https://blog.jverkamp.com/embeds/maker/christmas-tree-stand/stand.jpg">
&lt;/figure>

&lt;p>Kids are hard on just about everything. This time around, they managed to lose one of the three legs for their smaller Christmas tree. It&amp;rsquo;s not the sort of thing that&amp;rsquo;s particularly easy to find replacements for and even if you can it would probably cost about the same as the entire tree for shipping.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>So of course I had to model and 3D print my own!&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Links:&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>&lt;a href="https://blog.jverkamp.com/embeds/maker/christmas-tree-stand/christmas-tree-stand.f3d">Fusion 360 File&lt;/a>&lt;/li>
&lt;li>&lt;a href="https://blog.jverkamp.com/embeds/maker/christmas-tree-stand/christmas-tree-stand.stl">STL&lt;/a>&lt;/li>
